17
00:03:17.989 --> 00:03:19.115
MAN: Let down your hair.

18
00:03:22.160 --> 00:03:23.745
You do not pass for a boy.

19
00:03:27.248 --> 00:03:28.709
Let down your hair.

20
00:03:32.170 --> 00:03:33.880
(BREATHES HEAVILY)

21
00:03:40.303 --> 00:03:41.763
I am not afraid.

22
00:03:43.264 --> 00:03:45.139
Travelers spoke in these hills

23
00:03:45.141 --> 00:03:46.643
of the hero Robin Hood.

24
00:03:47.728 --> 00:03:49.145
He protects the meek.

25
00:03:57.195 --> 00:03:58.697
No one protects the meek.

26
00:04:00.782 --> 00:04:02.574
And he were no hero.

27
00:04:02.576 --> 00:04:06.035
He observed thrice a day
and gave silver to the poor.

28
00:04:06.037 --> 00:04:08.079
And he had the love
of Lady Marian.

29
00:04:08.081 --> 00:04:09.288
Is that not a hero?

30
00:04:09.290 --> 00:04:12.000
Lady Marian were taken
from an old shepherd's tale

31
00:04:12.002 --> 00:04:14.838
by a storyteller.
unfortunately. drunker than I.

32
00:04:15.881 --> 00:04:18.925
GIRL: She were the great love
of Robin Hood.

33
00:04:19.510 --> 00:04:20.719
ROBIN: Mmm.

34
00:04:22.262 --> 00:04:24.931
There is no great love
for one such as him.

35
00:04:28.519 --> 00:04:29.851
I have known
those who met this man.

36
00:04:29.853 --> 00:04:31.730
would you like
to know a secret?

37
00:04:32.981 --> 00:04:34.024
I would.

38
00:04:35.400 --> 00:04:37.318
He never prayed once
in his life.

39
00:04:39.029 --> 00:04:41.696
These tales
spread across the land

40
00:04:41.698 --> 00:04:43.784
are lies upon lies.

41
00:04:45.285 --> 00:04:47.744
He were a murderous brigand.

42
00:04:47.746 --> 00:04:49.829
who perhaps cut the throat
of a sheriff

43
00:04:49.831 --> 00:04:51.998
in a long line of others.

44
00:04:52.000 --> 00:04:54.169
People saw a meaning
where there was none.

45
00:04:55.629 --> 00:04:57.546
He was not a hero.

46
00:04:57.548 --> 00:04:59.673
He robbed and killed
for the joy of it.

47
00:04:59.675 --> 00:05:00.926
nothing more.

48
00:05:06.598 --> 00:05:07.849
Those you met...

49
00:05:09.810 --> 00:05:11.309
did they say he felt remorse

50
00:05:11.311 --> 00:05:12.395
for his crimes?

51
00:05:16.650 --> 00:05:18.652
I suspect he felt tired.

52
00:05:21.905 --> 00:05:25.532
I would say if you met
this villain Robin Hood.

53
00:05:25.534 --> 00:05:26.700
you should make haste away

54
00:05:26.702 --> 00:05:28.912
and keep whatever life
you have left here.

55
00:05:31.748 --> 00:05:33.917
-(BREATHING HEAVILY)
-(CLOTHES FLUTTER)

56
00:05:36.461 --> 00:05:38.672
(FOOTSTEPS RECEDE)

57
00:05:39.798 --> 00:05:42.217
(MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING)

58
00:05:58.483 --> 00:06:02.112
(PRAYING INDISTINCTLY)
...pardon of our sins.

59
00:06:03.947 --> 00:06:05.824
Through Jesus Christ our Lord.

60
00:06:07.450 --> 00:06:09.828
Amen. (BREATHING HEAVILY)

61
00:06:12.664 --> 00:06:14.833
(EERIE MUSIC PLAYING)

62
00:06:33.935 --> 00:06:36.104
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

63
00:07:03.965 --> 00:07:05.341
-(KNIFE SLASHING)
-(GIRL SCREAMING)

64
00:07:07.468 --> 00:07:09.429
(GIRL GURGLES)

65
00:07:12.641 --> 00:07:14.017
(GIRL CONTINUES GURGLING)

66
00:07:15.686 --> 00:07:17.312
Who was your kin?

67
00:07:19.815 --> 00:07:22.273
William Wainwright...
(INHALES SHARPLY)

68
00:07:22.275 --> 00:07:24.277
...of Pickering.
(INHALES SHARPLY)

69
00:07:24.820 --> 00:07:26.196
Pickering?

70
00:07:28.114 --> 00:07:29.488
-Father?
-(GIRL WHEEZING)

71
00:07:29.490 --> 00:07:30.949
(GURGLING)

72
00:07:30.951 --> 00:07:32.202
ROBIN: Grandfather?

73
00:07:37.666 --> 00:07:39.999
You should have bathed.

74
00:07:40.001 --> 00:07:41.670
or waited for the wind
to change.

75
00:07:44.422 --> 00:07:46.508
Or kept your weight
on your back foot.

76
00:07:48.885 --> 00:07:50.386
-That's all.
-(GAGGING)

77
00:07:50.887 --> 00:07:52.138
You did well.

78
00:07:56.101 --> 00:07:58.269
(SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING)

79
00:07:58.937 --> 00:08:00.271
(FLESH SQUELCHES)

80
00:08:01.439 --> 00:08:02.733
(EXHALES SOFTLY)

81
00:08:07.988 --> 00:08:10.864
(WIND BLOWING)

82
00:08:10.866 --> 00:08:13.034
(SOMBER MUSIC
